div.p:
As Children are virtually in their Parents before they are begotten and born into the World, ſo it hath pleaſed GOD to include Parents together with their Children in the Covenant. Thus it was under the firſt Covenant, the Covenant of Works made with Adam, "not for himſelf only, but for his Poſterity". And thus it is under the New Covenant, the Covenant of Grace. GOD promiſed Abraham, Gen. 17.7. I will eſtabliſh my covenant between me and thee, and thy ſeed after thee, in their generations for an everlaſting covenant;


to be a God unto thee, and to thy ſeed after thee. Which bleſſing is come on the believing Gentiles thro' JESUS CHRIST, Gal. 3.14. Let Parents then under the realizing view of the frailty of this life, make haſt to lay hold of GOD's Covenant, and to give up themſelves and their Seed to Him as their GOD, and that with their whole hearts; that whatever changes paſs over your Houſes, you may rejoyce with David, 2 Sam. 23.5. Although my houſe be not ſo with God; yet he hath made with me in everlaſting covenant, ordered in all things and ſure: for this is all my ſalvation, and all my deſire, although he make it not to grow. In this way, devote them to GOD, that He may own them as His Children, and take them up when you forſake them: In this way, bring them to CHRIST for His bleſſing, who ſaid, Suffer little Children, and forbid them not to come unto me: for of ſuch is the kingdom of heaven, Mat. 19.14. In this way, ſeek to GOD that they may be Saved by the waſhing of Regeneration, and the renewing of the Holy Ghoſt. Indeed, we can't ſay that all who are viſibly in Covenant obtain the inviſible Grace and ſaving Bleſſings of the Covenant: For they are not all Iſrael, which are of Iſrael, Rom. 9.6. Sad experience teacheth us that not a few have with profane Eſau deſpiſed the Birth-right. However, this is one of the means of Grace which that GOD hath appointed who alone can command the Bleſſing; and the conſideration of the uncertainty of our own lives as well as the lives of our Children,


ſhould make us ſpeedy and very ſerious in this Covenant tranſaction with GOD on their behalf, that we may in faith plead the Promiſes of GOD's Covenant for them, when we are about to be taken from them.
